# Intro
A reproduction of Smith et al. 2021 (MNRAS 506, 3882), Figure 2: four
co-located ionizing sources in a uniform 100 cm^-3 background, with a
10 pc-radius, 10^4 cm^-3 clump centered 20 pc away along +x (HEALPix
nside=1 pixel 4's center direction). Each source is 19.2 Msun
(Q_H ~ 2.5e48 s^-1), matching the paper's 4 sources totalling
Q_H ~ 1e49 s^-1 "equivalent to a typical O-type star".

See `../StromgrenSphereClump/` for the sibling example that instead
calibrates clump placement against this code's own measured (not
classical) ionization front reach -- useful when reproducing a specific
paper's absolute scale isn't the goal.

Density values (100 / 1e4 cm^-3), clump geometry (10 pc radius at 20 pc),
and `HII_region_rebuild_time_Myr=0.1` come directly from the paper. Gas
mass resolution follows Hu et al. 2017's convergence-test levels instead
of the paper's own 20 Msun (see Resolution below) since 20 Msun produces
no ionization at all with this code's algorithm.

The diffuse background and clump are set to different temperatures in
pressure equilibrium (`n*T` equal on both sides) by `makeIC_clump.py`'s
`--temperature` (background 1000 K by default, matching the paper).
`SPH:initial_temperature: 0` in params.yml is required for this --
otherwise it overwrites the per-particle IC values.

Box size (0.1 kpc / 100 pc) and `Stars:max_HII_search_radius` (45 pc) aren't stated explicitly in the paper for this test; chosen here to comfortably contain the clump (30 pc from the star) and its D-type expansion by t=8 Myr (the time of their Figure 2 snapshot) while staying under the box half-width.

## Resolution
Gas particle mass defaults to 4 Msun -- the coarsest of the four convergence-test resolutions in Hu et al. 2017 (Appendix A): 4, 0.5, 0.0625, 0.0078125 Msun. At this box size and background density, those correspond to roughly:

| mass [Msun] | diffuse particles | clump particles |      total     |
|-------------|-------------------|-----------------|----------------|
| 4.0         | 618k              | 259k            | 877k (default) |
| 0.5         | 4.9M              | 2.1M            | 7.0M           |
| 0.0625      | 39.5M             | 16.6M           | 56.1M          |
| 0.0078125   | 316.3M            | 132.5M          | 448.8M         |

At the default mass=4, the photon budget cannot afford to ionize even a
single gas particle at this density, so the run produces **zero
ionization** over the full 8 Myr regardless of `nside`. A finer mass is
required to see any HII region form. Generate ICs for the finer levels
with:
```
python3 makeIC_clump.py --mass 0.5       -o ICs_stromgren_clump.hdf5
python3 makeIC_clump.py --mass 0.0625    -o ICs_stromgren_clump.hdf5
python3 makeIC_clump.py --mass 0.0078125 -o ICs_stromgren_clump.hdf5
```
or `gas_mass=0.5 ./run.sh` etc. The two finer levels are cluster-scale runs, not intended to run on a laptop/workstation.

# Configure
```
./configure --disable-mpi --with-chemistry=GEAR_10 --with-feedback=GEAR --with-cooling=grackle_0 --with-stars=GEAR --with-sink=GEAR --with-star-formation=GEAR --with-kernel=wendland-C2 --with-grackle=path/to/grackle --with-chealpix=path/to/chealpix
```

```
make -j
```

# Run
`nside=0 ./run.sh` and `nside=1 ./run.sh` (use `run_name=nside0 ./run.sh` / `run_name=nside1 ./run.sh` to keep both outputs) run the geometry from Figure 2. At the default mass=4, this does *not* yet reproduce the panels (no ionization occurs -- see Resolution above); a finer mass is needed for that.

# Checking the redistribution effect and plotting

Same tools as `../StromgrenSphereClump/`:
```
python3 clump_anisotropy_check.py --nside0-snapshot nside0/snap/snapshot_0040.hdf5 --nside1-snapshot nside1/snap/snapshot_0040.hdf5
python3 plot_temperature_hii.py -s nside1/snap/snapshot -i 40
```
`clump_anisotropy_check.py` requires a build with `-DIONIZATION_FEEDBACK_DEBUG_NO_COOLING` (add to `CFLAGS` before `./configure`) so `IsIonizedFlags` accumulates monotonically instead of resetting every step.
